                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12705217" author="supun" created="Sat, 2 May 2009 03:38:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have attaches a simple fix for the WSDL endpoints.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12705282" author="ruwan" created="Sat, 2 May 2009 13:44:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Supun, I think this is not the proper fix for the issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems like the endpoint has not initialized. The EndpointContext cannot be null at any given time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ruwan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12705287" author="supun" created="Sat, 2 May 2009 14:19:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Ruwan,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;First thanks for looking at this quickly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you look at the AdressEndpoint it is checking the context before calling the onSuccess method. Since AdressEndpoint and WSDLEndpoint are functional wise same, I thought this is the correct solution. Also AdressEndpoint code was changed recently to check null, and the commit message says it has done it to avoid possible NPEs. I&apos;ll have a more deeper look.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Supun..&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12705292" author="supun" created="Sat, 2 May 2009 14:33:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Ruwan,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Send mediator is not implementing the ManagedLifeCycle interface. When WSDLEndpoint is specifiied inline within a Send mediator, since send mediator is not implementing the managed lifesycle WSDLEndpoint&apos;s init method is not called. Because of this when a WSDL endpoint is specified inline within a send mediator, it&apos;s endpoitn context is not created.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Supun.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12705295" author="ruwan" created="Sat, 2 May 2009 14:54:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think you got to the root cause of the issue and it seems to me that the Send Mediator has to be a ManagedLifecycle since it carries stuff with a managed life cycle.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ruwan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12705380" author="supun" created="Sun, 3 May 2009 03:48:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve attaced another patch with send mediator implementing managed life cycle. I didn&apos;t remove the null check in WSDLEndpoint, since it is better to anticipate the worse. Anyway I think the proper thing to do is throw an exception from the onSuccess method of the WSDLEndpoint if the context is not available.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12705768" author="veithen" created="Mon, 4 May 2009 21:38:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I added the ManagedLifecycle interface to SendMediator and this solves the issue. I did not apply the second part of the patch (the null check), because I think it&apos;s better to get a NPE than to silently skip part of the execution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks Supun for identifying and debugging this issue!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
